# Canonical standard for this repository

All AI-assisted work here must follow `.agents/AGENTS.md`. Treat that file as the single source of truth for
gates, artifacts, traceability, allowed tools, and co-governance.

This Cursor rule is an **adapter only**: it may add IDE-specific mechanics (for example how to invoke tools or
apply project rules). It must **not** contradict `.agents/AGENTS.md`. If anything conflicts, defer to
`.agents/AGENTS.md` and tell the human about the mismatch.

To dive deeper, open `.agents/AGENTS.md` first, then persona files under `.agents/agents/` and concepts under
`.agents/concepts/` as the task requires.
